[[General]] '''Michail Kostarakos''' ({{lang-el|Μιχαήλ Κωσταράκος}}, born 1956) is a [[Hellenic Army]] officer who served as the Chief of the [[Hellenic National Defence General Staff]] in 2011–2015. He is the designated Chairman of the [[European Union Military Committee]], taking office from 6 November 2015.
== Life and career == Michail Kostarakos was born in [[Thessaloniki]] in February 1956. He is the son of [[Major General]] Dimitrios Kostarakos, who fought in the [[Greek Civil War]] and the [[Korean War]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Michalis Kostarakos |url=http://veteranos.gr/anachorise-gia-tin-teleftea-tou-metathesi-o-ipostratigos-d-kostarakos/ |title=Αναχώρησε για την "τελευταία του μετάθεση" ο Υποστράτηγος Δ.Κωσταράκος &#124;veteranos &#124;Εθνικά Θέματα |publisher=Veteranos.gr |date=2013-10-17 |accessdate=2015-07-26}}</ref> He completed his school studies in the [[University of Thessaloniki]]'s Experimental School, before enrolling in the [[Hellenic Army Academy]] in 1974, from which he graduated in 1978 as a [[Second Lieutenant]] of [[Artillery]].<ref name="Bio">{{cite web | url = http://www.geetha.mil.gr/el/leadership-el/cv-el/cat-former-chiefs/%CE%BC%CE%B7%CF%87%CE%B1%CE%AE%CE%BB-%CE%BA%CF%89%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B1%CF%81%CE%AC%CE%BA%CE%BF%CF%82.html | title = Βιογραφικά Ηγεσίας: Αρχηγός ΓΕΕΘΑ | publisher = Hellenic National Defence General Staff | language = Greek | accessdate = 15 September 2015}}</ref> Kostarakos served in various posts in both field and especially anti-aircraft artillery (the [[MIM-23 Hawk]] system), attended various schools and academies (including the US Army's Hawk course at [[Fort Bliss]]), as well as in senior staff positions in NATO's International Military Staff, the [[Kosovo Force|KFOR]]'s Joint Operation Center, and Greece's [[NDC-GR]].<ref name="Bio"/>
As a field officer (Brigadier General in 2006), he commanded the [[96th National Guard Higher Command (Greece)|96th National Guard Higher Command]] at [[Chios]], the 3rd Bureau and the Operations Command of the [[Hellenic Army General Staff]], the [[12th Mechanized Infantry Division (Greece)|12th Mechanized Infantry Division]], and finally the III Army Corps/NDC-GR, before being promoted to full General and assuming the post of Chief of the [[Hellenic National Defence General Staff]] on 1 November 2011.<ref name="Bio"/> On 13 November 2014 he was elected as the next Chairman of the [[European Union Military Committee]], with a three-year tenure starting from November 2015.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.tovima.gr/en/article/?aid=650547 | title = General Kostarakos elected president of the EU Military Committee | publisher = [[To Vima]] | date = 14 November 2014 | accessdate = 14 November 2014}}</ref>
He has been awarded with several distinctions, including the Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Phoenix (Greece)|Order of the Phoenix]], the Grand Commander of the [[Order of Honour (Greece)|Order of Honour]], the [[Armenia]]n Medal for Military Co-operation, and the [[NATO Medal]] for the Balkans.<ref name="Bio"/> General Kostarakos is married and has two daughters.<ref name="Bio"/> He also speaks English and French, has completed a graduate degree in the Law School of the [[University of Athens]], and holds a post-graduate degree in Diplomatic and Strategic Studies.<ref name="Bio"/>
On 20 August 2015, the [[Government Council for Foreign Affairs and Defence]] decided the retirement of Kostarakos and his replacement with the hitherto Chief of the [[Hellenic Navy General Staff]], Vice Admiral [[Evangelos Apostolakis]], taking effect on 15 September. Kostarakos was immediately recalled to active duty pending his assumption of the post of Chairman of the European Union Military Committee,<ref>{{cite news | url = http://news.in.gr/greece/article/?aid=1500019767 | title = Νέος αρχηγός ΓΕΕΘΑ ο αντιναύαρχος Ευάγγελος Αποστολάκης | publisher = in.gr | language = Greek | date = 20 August 2015 | accessdate = 22 August 2015}}</ref> which took place on 6 November 2015.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://eeas.europa.eu/csdp/structures-instruments-agencies/eumc/chairman-eumc/index_en.htm | title = The Chairman of the European Union Military Committee (CEUMC) | publisher = European External Action Service | accessdate = 18 August 2016}}</ref>
